subject:

FINAL OUTCOME OF FAITH--ETERNAL LIFE (read:Col. 1:9-14)
===================================================================
verse:

With joy, 11c giving thanks to the Father, who has qualified
you to share in the inheritance of the saints of light.
(Col. 1:12)

===================================================================
reflection:

[qualified you] Sin disqualifies us. But God qualified us
through Christ’s redemption (vs. 14). The word [inheritance]
recalls the inheritance of the Promised Land that was
allotted to the families of Israel according to God’s
promises and not because of their righteous- ness [Deut.
9:5]. [saints in light] Are believers who are no longer
separated from God, who is light (Jn. 8:12).

===================================================================
prayer:

Father, thank You that through Christ's redemption You have
qualified us for Your inheritance, not because of our
righteousness but because of Your promises. Bring us from
darkness into Your marvelous light, and help us to walk as
saints who are no longer separated from You. Let our lives
reflect the privilege of belonging to Your kingdom. Amen.
(AI)

===================================================================
